        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Dorothy Krampitz Evarts served as a civil service worker during World War II in Oahu, Hawaii. Dorothy Evarts joined her husband, a reservist, in Hawaii some time after the December 7, 1941 bombing of Pearl Harbor. While in Hawaii the couple worked for the government, and lived in Navy housing. Mr. Evarts drove supply trucks, and Dorothy worked posting supplies for ships arriving and departing Pearl Harbor’s Naval Shipyard. She continued working until her departure soon after VJ Day.</p>
        </bioghist>
